IRS990.MissionDesc: THE GIRL SCOUTS OF HAWAII'S PRIMARY EXEMPT PURPOSE IS TO HELP GIRLS DEVELOP THEIR FULLEST POTENTIAL THROUGH GROUP EXPERIENCE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE COUNCIL IS A NOT-FOR-PROFIT ORGANIZATION DESCRIBED IN THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE (IRC) SECTION 501(C)(3) AND IS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL AND STATE INCOME TAXES ON RELATED INCOME PURSUANT TO IRC SECTION 501(A) AND THE RELATED SECTIONS OF THE HAWAII REVISED STATUTES. THEREFORE, ONLY UNRELATED BUSINESS INCOME, AS DEFINED IN IRC SECTION 512(A)(1) IS SUBJECT TO FEDERAL AND STATE INCOME TAXES. THE COUNCIL RECOGNIZES THE EFFECT OF INCOME TAX POSITIONS ONLY IF IT IS MORE-LIKELY-THAN-NOT THAT THE TAX POSITION WILL BE SUSTAINED ON EXAMINATION BY TAX AUTHORITIES, BASED ON THE TECHNICAL MERITS OF THE POSITION. CHANGES IN RECOGNITION OR MEASUREMENT ARE REFLECTED IN THE PERIOD IN WHICH THE CHANGE IN JUDGMENT OCCURS. THE COUNCIL HAS EVALUATED ITS TAX POSITIONS AND DETERMINED THAT THERE WERE NO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS AS OF SEPTEMBER 30, 2018. FOR YEARS BEFORE 2015, THE COUNCIL IS NO LONGER SUBJECT TO U.S. FEDERAL INCOME TAX EXAMINATIONS.
GRANTS OR ASSISTANCE WERE MADE TO GIRL SCOUTS FOR PAYMENT OF MEMBERSHIP FEES AND FOR PARTICIPATING IN VARIOUS GIRL SCOUTS' PROGRAMS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CEO COMPENSATION WAS SET BY THE "EXECUTIVE SEARCH COMMITTEE" AT THE TIME THE CURRENT CEO WAS HIRED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE PROVIDED TO BOARD VOLUNTEERS DURING ORIENTATION. THESE DOCUMENTS ARE PROVIDED TO THE GENERAL PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.

THE ORGANIZATION HAS AN AUDIT COMMITTEE THAT ASSUMES RESPONSIBILITY FOR OVERSIGHT OF THE AUDIT OF ITS FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND SELECTION OF AN INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTANT. THE PROCESS HAS NOT CHANGED FROM PRIOR YEAR.
